The real deal if you order off the menu written only in Chinese.  Authentic mostly Shanghainese food (with about a third Sichuan dishes and a sprinkling of Cantonese dishes) that I've yet to find any where else in Phoenix.  Check out the pics for my best attempt at translation of the menu, which is by no means 100% accurate so please refer to the restaurant for a detailed description.  Alex C already listed all the stuff we ordered so please refer to his review for details.  The only one he didn't really talk about is the veggie dish called Ma Lan Tou which refers to the type of Shanghainese vegetable that I've rarely seen outside of China.  It's a cold 'salad' of finely chopped said dark green leafy vegetable and firm tofu tossed in sesame oil.  A refreshing summer appetizer which great contrast of crunchiness from the vegetable and softness of the tofu.  See item (x) on the menu.

