g_kOqG2Zl8ygx46XKtWilw
家在陝西 (literally: Home in Shaanxi) New ownership since 7/1/15. Ignore all prior photos, reviews and please do not come here for American Chinese food esp egg rolls.  New owners kept the English name to probably save time & money but can be very misleading to those who don't read Chinese.  This is legit Northern Chinese food so do some research before coming otherwise it can be overwhelming. Servers speak limited English so don't expect too much help from them. Check out my photos for ideas.  Go with a group if possible. Portions are generous especially #17-#19: ma-la spicy chicken, shrimp with smoky roasted chiles and spicy fish stew - all spectacular dishes worthy for celebrations. Food can be quite spicy but is very well balanced and expertly executed. It can get packed during peak hours so try going off hours but not during their 2:30-4:30 break. BBQ is only served after 4:30.

